@startuml
title Features: Authentication & User Provisioning
skinparam maxMessageSize 150
autonumber

actor "User / Admin" as User
participant "Browser (Vue SPA)" as Browser
participant "Laravel (BFF)" as BFF
participant "Microsoft Entra ID" as EntraID
participant "ERP/CRM API" as API
database "PostgreSQL (Local)" as DB

== Feature 1, 2: Login & Just-In-Time Provisioning ==

User -> Browser: Click "Login with Microsoft"
Browser -> BFF: GET /login
BFF -> Browser: Redirect to Entra ID (OIDC)
User -> EntraID: Authenticate
EntraID -> BFF: Callback with Auth Code
BFF -> EntraID: Exchange Code for Access & Refresh Tokens
EntraID -> BFF: Tokens & User Profile (Email, Name, Roles)

BFF -> DB: Check if User Exists locally (Local DB / Cache)
alt User Exists (Admin pre-provisioning)
    BFF -> DB: Fetch Local Profile & Settings
else User Does Not Exist (New user in portal)
    BFF -> DB: Create new User Record (JIT Provisioning)
    BFF -> EntraID: Add User to "Hospital-Users" Group (via Graph API)
    EntraID -> BFF: Group assignment successful
end

note over BFF, DB: Token Management
BFF -> BFF: Store Refresh Token securely (Encrypted/DB)
BFF -> Browser: Create Laravel Session (HttpOnly Auth Cookie)

== Ongoing Session & Token Refresh ==

Browser -> BFF: Authenticated API Request (Session Cookie)
BFF -> BFF: Validate internal Session
alt Access Token is Expired
    BFF -> EntraID: Exchange Refresh Token for new Access Token
    EntraID -> BFF: New Access Token
    BFF -> BFF: Update Access Token in Storage
end
BFF -> API: Forward request to Microservices with Valid Token

== Role Management & Super User Assignments ==

note over User, EntraID: Roles & Groups managed uniquely in Entra ID
User -> EntraID: Add/Remove Role or Change Group
EntraID -> EntraID: Update Identity Token
EntraID -> Browser: Invalidate Session and Token (Token revocation)
Browser -> BFF: Re-authentication Required

note over User, EntraID: Feature 8: Assign Super User for multi-PDV
User -> EntraID: Add User to "SuperUser-Hospital-{X}" Group (native Entra management)
EntraID -> EntraID: Update Group Membership & Identity Token
note over BFF: On next login, BFF reads groups from token\nand provisions Super User access for associated PDVs
Browser -> BFF: User logs in / token refreshed
BFF -> BFF: Extract groups from identity token
BFF -> Browser: Super User status now active for assigned PDVs

@enduml
